---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import OverviewFlow from "../../components/OverviewFlow.astro";
---

<Layout title="概要 | 吊り荷Yaw制御" lang="en">
    <main class="overview-page">
        <section class="overview-intro">
            <h1>Overview</h1>
            <p>
                In this project, we built a payload control environment, trained a reinforcement learning–based control model,
                developed a camera-based yaw estimation model, and finally integrated both models for demonstration on a Raspberry Pi.
                The final system successfully controlled the payload yaw under external disturbances.
            </p>
            <OverviewFlow lang="en" />
        </section>

        <section id="environment" class="overview-item">
            <h2>Payload Control Environment</h2>
            <p>
                A simulation environment was developed that includes the control unit,
                suspended payloads (truss, H-beam, and plate), ropes, and a crane.
                The environment supports multiple payload configurations and external disturbance conditions for
                both development and performance evaluation.
            </p>
            <div class="overview-images">
                <figure>
                    <img
                        src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/overview/thrusters.png`}
                        alt="Payload control unit with four thrusters"
                    />
                </figure>
                <figure>
                    <img
                        src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/overview/truss.png`}
                        alt="Truss payload used for control experiments"
                    />
                </figure>
            </div>      
            <div class="overview-next">
                <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/en/environment/`}>
                    Environment Details →
                </a>
            </div>
        </section> 
        <section id="control-model" class="overview-item">
            <h2>Control Model Training</h2>
            <p>
                A reinforcement learning–based control model was trained to rotate the suspended payload to the target yaw angle.
                Representative control results are shown below under X-direction (X1Y0) and X/Y-direction (X1Y1) disturbance conditions.
                The model successfully achieved the target yaw under both disturbance conditions.
            </p>
            <div class="result-images">
                <img
                    src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/overview/chart_01.png`}
                    alt="Yaw control results under X1Y0 disturbance conditions"
                />
                <img
                    src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/overview/chart_02.png`}
                    alt="Yaw control results under X1Y1 disturbance conditions"
                />
            </div>
            <div class="overview-next">
                <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/en/control_model/`}>
                    Control Model Details →
                </a>
            </div>      
        </section>

        <section id="yaw-estimation" class="overview-item">
            <h2>Yaw Estimation</h2>
            <p>
                A camera mounted on the control unit captures images used to estimate the payload yaw angle.
                Colored hooks are first detected, and image-processing methods tailored to each payload geometry are then applied to determine the yaw angle.
                The examples below show the estimation process for the H-beam, plate, and truss payloads.
            </p>
            <figure class="feature-image">
                <img
                    src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/overview/yaw-estimation.png`}
                    alt="Yaw estimation examples for H-beam, plate, and truss payloads"
                    loading="lazy"
                />
            </figure>      
            <div class="overview-next">
                <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/en/yaw_estimation/`}>
                    Yaw Estimation Details →
                </a>
            </div>      
        </section>

        <section id="raspberry-pi" class="overview-item">
            <h2>Vision-Based Control</h2>
            <p>
                The payload yaw estimation model and the reinforcement learning–based control model were integrated and executed on a Raspberry Pi.
                The results below compare the Raspberry Pi implementation with the development environment under identical disturbance conditions,
                demonstrating equivalent control performance.
            </p>
            <div class="result-images">
                <img
                    src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/overview/Pi_chart_01.png`}
                    alt="Control results in the development environment"
                />
                <img
                    src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/overview/Pi_chart_02.png`}
                    alt="Control results on Raspberry Pi"
                />
            </div>
            <div class="overview-next">
                <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/en/raspberry_pi/`}>
                    Vision-Based Control Details →
                </a>
            </div>            
        </section>
    </main>
</Layout>

<style>
    .overview-page {
    width: min(100% - 40px, 1000px);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 48px 0 0px;
    }

    .overview-intro h1 {
    margin: 0 0 24px;
    font-size: clamp(32px, 5vw, 46px);
    font-weight: 500;
    }

    .overview-intro p,
    .overview-item p {
    margin: 0 0 18px;
    font-size: 18px;
    line-height: 1.9;
    }

    .overview-item {
    padding: 36px 0;
    border-top: 1px solid #ddd;
    }

    .overview-item h2 {
    margin: 0 0 16px;
    font-size: clamp(24px, 3vw, 30px);
    font-weight: 500;
    }

    @media (max-width: 700px) {
    .overview-page {
        width: min(100% - 28px, 1000px);
        padding-top: 32px;
    }

    .overview-intro p,
    .overview-item p {
        font-size: 16px;
        line-height: 1.8;
    }
    }

    .overview-images {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.45fr;
    gap: 4px;
    margin: 24px 0;
    align-items: stretch;
    }

    .overview-images figure {
    margin: 0;
    }

    .overview-images img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    }

    @media (max-width: 700px) {
    .overview-images {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }


    .overview-images img {
        height: auto;
    }
    }  

    .overview-next {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: flex-end;
    margin: 16px 0 0px;
    }

    .overview-next a {
    color: inherit;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 500;
    }

    .overview-next a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
    }

    .environment-images {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.45fr;
        gap: 8px;
    }
    .result-images {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        gap: 8px;
    }

    .result-images img {
        width: 100%;
        height: auto;
        display: block;
    }

    .feature-image {
        margin: 0;
    }

    .feature-image img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    }
</style>